catalogue_data.learning_objectives:
Upon completion of the course, students will be able to:
- independently prepare biological specimens, operate light microscopes, and document microscopic observations clearly and systematically;
- explain the relationship between plant structure and function at the cellular, tissue, and organ levels, and illustrate these correlations using concrete examples;
- describe how plant anatomy is interconnected with systematics, physiology, ecology, and development, and discuss these links in a biological context.

